<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,340,295,320]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Seasonality.</emphasis>
In the Ligurian Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Boero" box="[583,812,295,320]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Boero, F. &amp; Fresi, E. (1986) Zonation and evolution of a Rocky bottom hydroid community. Marine Ecology, 7 (2), 123 - 150. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0485.1986. tb 00152. x" type="journal article" year="1986">
Boero &amp; Fresi 
<number box="[755,812,295,320]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) from October to April (
<bibRefCitation author="Boero" box="[1095,1326,295,320]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Boero, F. &amp; Fresi, E. (1986) Zonation and evolution of a Rocky bottom hydroid community. Marine Ecology, 7 (2), 123 - 150. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0485.1986. tb 00152. x" type="journal article" year="1986">
Boero &amp; Fresi 
<number box="[1267,1326,295,320]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Boero 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[190,250,332,357]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1986.0">1986</number>
), and January–May, July–December (Puce 
<emphasis box="[751,811,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[820,881,332,356]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2009.0">2009</number>
); all year in Salento waters (De Vito 
<number box="[1321,1380,332,357]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2006.0">2006</number>
; this study).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,455,404,429]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Reproductive period.</emphasis>
In the Mediterranean, fertile colonies can be found all year round (
<bibRefCitation author="Pena" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Garcia Carrascosa, A. M. (2002) The benthic hydroid fauna of the Chafarinas Islands (Alboran Sea, western Mediterranean). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden, 337, 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="2002">
Peña Cantero &amp; García Carrascosa 
<number box="[367,426,440,464]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert" box="[440,635,439,464]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Schuchert, P. (2008 b) The European athecate hydroids and their medusae (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria): Filifera Part 4. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 115 (4), 677 - 757." type="journal article" year="2008" yearSuffix="b">
Schuchert 
<number box="[562,622,439,464]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2008.0">2008</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
), but the peak of reproduction seems to be during autumn and winter (
<bibRefCitation author="Boero" box="[158,295,476,500]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Boero, F. (1984) The ecology of marine hydroids and effects of environmental factors: a review. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli I, Marine Ecology, 5 (2), 93 - 118. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0485.1984. tb 00310. x" type="journal article" year="1984">
Boero 
<number box="[236,295,476,500]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Boero 
<emphasis box="[382,438,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[445,504,476,501]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1986.0">1986</number>
; De Vito 
<number box="[610,669,476,501]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2006.0">2006</number>
; Puce 
<emphasis box="[742,799,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[805,864,476,500]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2009.0">2009</number>
; this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,511,536]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Distribution.</emphasis>
Rather common and widespread in the western and eastern Mediterranean, including the African and 
<collectingCountry box="[198,268,548,573]" name="Israel" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Israeli</collectingCountry>
coasts (
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert" box="[357,553,548,573]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Schuchert, P. (2008 b) The European athecate hydroids and their medusae (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria): Filifera Part 4. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 115 (4), 677 - 757." type="journal article" year="2008" yearSuffix="b">
Schuchert 
<number box="[478,538,548,573]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2008.0">2008</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
); Northeastern Atlantic, Indo-Pacific (distribution probably wider; it resembles the species 
<taxonomicName box="[280,415,585,608]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eudendriidae" genus="Eudendrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="ramosum">
<emphasis box="[280,415,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">E. ramosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and many records under this name could possibly belong to 
<taxonomicName box="[1102,1269,583,608]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eudendriidae" genus="Eudendrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="glomeratum">
<emphasis box="[1102,1269,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">E. glomeratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,433,620,645]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Records in Salento.</emphasis>
Common at Porto Cesareo (
<bibRefCitation author="Faucci" box="[760,1012,620,645]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Faucci, A. &amp; Boero, F. (2000) Structure of an epiphytic hydroid community on Cystoseira at two sites of different wave exposure. In: Mills, C. E., Boero, F., Migotto, A. &amp; Gili, J. M. (Eds.), Trends in Hydrozoan Biology - IV. Scientia Marina, 64 (Supplement 1), pp. 255 - 264. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2000.64 s 1255" type="journal article" year="2000">
Faucci &amp; Boero 
<number box="[952,1012,620,644]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and Otranto (De Vito 
<number box="[1284,1343,620,645]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2006.0">2006</number>
; Gravili 
<number box="[151,211,655,680]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2006.0">2006</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravili" box="[221,443,655,680]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Gravili, C., Boero, F. &amp; Licandro, P. (2008 a) Hydrozoa. Biologia Marina Mediterranea, 15 (Supplement), 71 - 91." type="journal article" year="2008" yearSuffix="a">
Gravili 
<emphasis box="[308,357,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[371,430,656,680]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2008.0">2008</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
; this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
